# Employee personality bundles (mandatory)

Employees are listed in **`personas/employees.txt`** (e.g. `alex`, `tim`). Each has **`.cursor/rules/<name>-*.mdc`** and a rendered **`.cursor/personas/<name>-personality.md`** for Slack / future runtimes.

**`bimross-company.mdc`** is prepended into **every** employee bundle (shared BimRoss identity). After editing it, run **`./scripts/sync-employee-personality.sh --all`**.

After editing **any** `<name>-*.mdc` for that employee:

1. **`./scripts/sync-employee-personality.sh --employee <name>`** (or **`--all`** for everyone).
2. Commit the **`*.mdc`** change(s) and the updated **`-personality.md`** together.

CI runs **`./scripts/check-employee-personality.sh`**. Production (e.g. **Alex** in **employee-factory**) reads **`alex-personality.md`** from the **`geeemoney/cursor-rules`** image.

**Docs:** **`docs/employee-agents.md`**, **`docs/persona-vs-policy.md`**, **`docs/agents-capabilities.md`**.

**Optional:** uncomment lines in **`.cursorignore`** for `*-personality.md` while editing—still commit tracked bundles.

Full policy: **`cursor-rules-maintenance.mdc`** (employee bundles).
